									<h3><strong>Effective Date: January 1st, 2025</strong></h3><p>At The Garden of Great Ideas, we value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share your information when you access or use our platform, and outlines the choices you have regarding your information.</p><p>By using The Garden of Great Ideas, you agree to the collection and use of your personal information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.</p><h3><strong>1. Information We Collect</strong></h3><p>We collect various types of information to provide and improve our services to you. The information we collect includes:</p><ul><li><strong>Personal Information</strong>: When you create an account or interact with the platform, you may provide personal details such as your name, email address, and other contact information.</li><li><strong>Content You Submit</strong>: Any ideas, dreams, or other content you upload or share on the platform (e.g., project descriptions, images, etc.) will be collected and stored by The Garden of Great Ideas.</li><li><strong>Usage Data</strong>: We collect information on how you use and interact with the platform, including your IP address, browser type, device information, pages you visit, and actions you take on the platform.</li><li><strong>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</strong>: We use cookies, web beacons, and other tracking technologies to improve the functionality of our platform, personalize your experience, and analyze usage patterns.</li></ul><h3><strong>2. How We Use Your Information</strong></h3><p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p><ul><li><strong>To Provide and Improve Services</strong>: To operate, maintain, and improve The Garden of Great Ideas and its features, such as allowing you to plant, explore, and collaborate on ideas.</li><li><strong>To Communicate with You</strong>: To send you updates, newsletters, promotional content, and respond to your inquiries.</li><li><strong>To Personalize Your Experience</strong>: To customize content and recommendations based on your preferences, past interactions, and interests.</li><li><strong>To Ensure Security</strong>: To monitor the platform for security purposes, detect fraud or misuse, and prevent abuse of the platform.</li><li><strong>To Comply with Legal Obligations</strong>: To comply with applicable laws, regulations, and legal processes.</li></ul><h3><strong>3. Sharing Your Information</strong></h3><p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes without your explicit consent. However, we may share your information in the following circumstances:</p><ul><li><strong>With Service Providers</strong>: We may share your information with trusted third-party companies that help us operate the platform, such as payment processors, hosting services, and analytics providers. These third parties are required to maintain the confidentiality of your information.</li><li><strong>With Other Users</strong>: Any content you submit (e.g., ideas, project descriptions, etc.) will be visible to other users of The Garden of Great Ideas. Please be mindful of the information you share publicly.</li><li><strong>For Legal and Security Reasons</strong>: We may disclose your information if required by law or to protect the rights, safety, or property ofThe Garden of Great Ideas, our users, or others.</li><li><strong>Business Transfers</strong>: If The Garden of Great Ideas is involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your personal information may be transferred as part of that transaction.</li></ul><h3><strong>4. Your Choices</strong></h3><p>You have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p><ul><li><strong>Access and Update</strong>: You can access, review, and update the information in your account settings at any time.</li><li><strong>Delete Your Account</strong>: You can delete your account by contacting us. Please note that deleting your account will not remove content you’ve shared publicly or shared with other users.</li><li><strong>Opt-Out of Communications</strong>: You can opt-out of receiving promotional emails by following the unsubscribe link in our emails or by updating your email preferences in your account settings.</li><li><strong>Cookies</strong>: Most browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings. You can choose to disable cookies, but doing so may limit your ability to use certain features of the platform.</li></ul><h3><strong>5. Data Retention</strong></h3><p>We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to provide the services you request, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements. If you delete your account, we will retain certain information for legal and operational purposes, but it will not be used for marketing or other non-essential activities.</p><h3><strong>6. Data Security</strong></h3><p>We use reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect the information we collect from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, please be aware that no data transmission over the internet can be guaranteed to be 100% secure, and we cannot ensure the security of any information you transmit to us.</p><h3><strong>7. International Transfers</strong></h3><p>If you are accessing The Garden of Great Ideas from outside the USA, your personal information may be transferred to and processed in [Your Country], where our servers and central databases are located. By using The Garden of Great Ideas, you consent to the transfer of your information to countries outside of your own.</p><h3><strong>8. Children’s Privacy</strong></h3><p>The Garden of Great Ideas is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we learn that we have inadvertently collected personal information from a child under 18, we will take steps to delete that information as soon as possible.</p><h3><strong>9. Changes to this Privacy Policy</strong></h3><p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make changes, we will post the updated policy on this page and update the “Effective Date” at the top of the document. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any updates.</p><h3><strong>10. Contact Us</strong></h3><p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at <span style="color: #ffffff;"><a style="color: #ffffff;" href="mailto:info@thegardenofgreatideas.com.">info@thegardenofgreatideas.com.</a></span></p><h3><strong>Acceptance of Privacy Policy</strong></h3><p>By using The Garden of Great Ideas, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.</p>								</div>
